        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 4:19AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 418 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm in
southwestern Crockett County, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ozona, The Intersection Of Ranch Road 2083 And Highway 405, The
Intersection Of Highway 163 And Ranch Road 1973, Ft Lancaster, The
Intersection Of I-10 And Highway 405, The Intersection Of I-10 And
Highway 290, and I-10 Near The Crockett-Sutton County Line.

This includes Interstate 10 between Mile Markers 332 and 379.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
